    "name": {
      "name": "SAM hydroxide adenosyltransferase C-terminal domain",
      "short": "SAM_HAT_C"
    },
    "description": [
      {
        "text": "<p>This is a family of proteins, previously known as DUF62, found in archaebacteria and bacteria. The structure of proteins in this family is similar to that of a bacterial fluorinating enzyme [[cite:PUB00047427]]. S-adenosyl-l-methionine hydroxide adenosyltransferases utilises a rigorously conserved amino acid side chain triad (Asp-Arg-His) which may have a role in activating water to hydroxide ion [[cite:PUB00054078]]. This family used to be known as DUF62. This entry represents the C-terminal domain of these enzymes.</p>",
